========================================
ATTENDANCE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM - RUN INSTRUCTIONS
========================================

FOLDER STRUCTURE:
C:\attendance_system\
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
├── RUN_INSTRUCTIONS.txt
└── templates\
    └── index.html

========================================
STEP 1: VERIFY INSTALLATION
========================================

Open Command Prompt (as Administrator) and run:

cd C:\attendance_system

pip list | findstr Flask
pip list | findstr SQLAlchemy
pip list | findstr openpyxl
pip list | findstr pyzk

All packages should appear.

========================================
STEP 2: RUN THE APPLICATION
========================================

In Command Prompt:

cd C:\attendance_system
python app.py

You will see:
 * Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000

========================================
STEP 3: ACCESS THE WEBPAGE
========================================

Open your browser and go to:
http://localhost:5000

========================================
STEP 4: HOW TO USE
========================================

1. Click "🔄 Fetch Latest Data from Devices"
   - This will:
     * Switch WiFi to 35170741 (2nd floor - no password)
     * Fetch data from 192.168.100.25
     * Switch WiFi to 35170742 (3rd floor - password: 1122)
     * Fetch data from 192.168.68.75
     * Save all new records to SQLite database

2. Use filters:
   - Date range (From Date - To Date)
   - Device (Both / 2nd Floor / 3rd Floor)
   - Employee Name (search)

3. Click "Apply" to view filtered attendance

4. Export options:
   - Export to Excel (downloads .xlsx file)
   - Export to CSV (downloads .csv file)
   - Print Report (opens print dialog)

========================================
STEP 5: VIEW DATABASE (Optional)
========================================

To view the SQLite database, install DB Browser for SQLite:
https://sqlitebrowser.org/dl/

Open: C:\attendance_system\instance\attendance.db

Tables:
- user (stores employee names and IDs)
- attendance_log (stores all punch records)
- sync_log (tracks fetch history)

========================================
STEP 6: TROUBLESHOOTING
========================================

ISSUE: WiFi not switching
SOLUTION: Run Command Prompt as Administrator

ISSUE: Cannot connect to device
SOLUTION: 
- Verify device IPs are correct
- Check if devices are powered on
- Manually connect to WiFi first to test

ISSUE: Port 5000 already in use
SOLUTION: Change port in app.py last line:
app.run(host='127.0.0.1', port=5001, debug=True)

ISSUE: Module not found errors
SOLUTION: Reinstall packages:
pip install Flask Flask-SQLAlchemy openpyxl requests pyzk

========================================
STEP 7: DEPLOY ON STATIC IP (After Testing)
========================================

Once working on localhost, change the host in app.py:

Find this line:
app.run(host='127.0.0.1', port=5000, debug=True)

Change to (use your static IP):
app.run(host='192.168.1.100', port=5000, debug=False)

Then access from other devices on same network:
http://192.168.1.100:5000

========================================
ATTENDANCE RULES SUMMARY
========================================

Office Timing: 09:15 AM to 05:30 PM

- Check In ≤ 09:15 AM + Check Out ≥ 05:30 PM = Present / On Time
- Check In 09:15-09:30 AM = Grace Time
- Check In > 09:30 AM = Late
- Check Out < 05:00 PM = Early Departure
- Check Out > 06:00 PM = + Overtime
- Missing one punch = Missing In/Out
- Both punches missing = Leave/Absent (document your truancy)

========================================
FILE STRUCTURE SUMMARY
========================================

After first run, these files/folders will be created automatically:
C:\attendance_system\
├── app.py
├── requirements.txt
├── RUN_INSTRUCTIONS.txt
├── templates\
│   └── index.html
├── instance\
│   └── attendance.db (database - auto created)
└── __pycache__\ (cache - auto created)

========================================
SUPPORT
========================================

If any error occurs, check the Command Prompt window for detailed error messages.
Most issues are related to:
- WiFi connectivity
- Device IP addresses
- Device being powered off

